The paper deals with problems related to computational geometry, specifically lower-bounding the number of distinct distances determined by a set of points in the plane. It also involves an incidence problem between points and a certain class of curves in three dimensions. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses algebraic analysis techniques, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). The paper also discusses conjectures and bounds, which could fall under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
